Interface ProjectLib.MessageHandling

  • Enclosing class:
    ProjectLib

    public static interface ProjectLib.MessageHandling
    MessageHandling interface. This is an optional interface that can be exported by a class to asynchronously recieve messages. This interface defines a callback method that is called to deliver a message to your node.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean deliverMessage(ProjectLib.Message msg)
      Callback called when message received.

    • Method Detail

      • deliverMessage

        boolean deliverMessage(ProjectLib.Message msg)
        Callback called when message received. Argument is the message, including source address and body. Function should return True if it handled the message, or False if it did not. On False, the message is added to the receive queue, and can be delivered to a getMessage call.
        Parameters:
        msg - Message received, with addr set to source
        Returns:
        return false if message was not handled and needs to be added to receive queue
